item.title: GovBrief Today #275
item.description: Donors and power grabs take precedence in Donald Trump's world. Just one day after the UN condemned the US for attacking boats and killing people, the Trump administration announced a brand new attack. They even had an attorney tell Congress that it didn't need their authority to do so. They also acknowledged that dozens of secret donors to what they call The Donald J. Trump Ballroom may remain anonymous while paying for a White House extension. That's no different than a wealthy tech executive paying for the Las Vegas police to add 10 Cybertrucks to its fleet, which just happened. Private entities aren't supposed to buy things for the government. While rich donors build Trump a gilded ballroom at the White House, 40 million Americans are waiting for food aid the government refuses to pay, even though $5.25 billion is available right now. A federal judge had to order them to start. But this is the same administration that told Congress today it could kill without consequences or investigation. This is un-American. item.title: Return of the Meme: 1513 (Sunday Wizardposting)
item.description:
Let's get this bread.
Finished the night waking up from a nightmare where I was trapped with a class at a smaller airport because of wind and we were on our way to (what turned out to be) a sentient evil island and when I asked why the fuck we were going there, it was because "the sacrifice brings in money from rich donors to the school." Also at some point it intersected with the universe of the original Frasier.
Ah yes. The famous Zantine Empire, sequel to the Reman Empire.
I really need to try this at some point.
Pippin tax! Today's message from Pippin: [whispered] "Pippin. Pippin." ______ 1) Are you on the run to a safe place and passing through Arizona on your way to safer grounds? My apartment is open to you to crash at, and it is a safe space. Pippin and I will make you a meal and gladly share tea, wine, or mead with you. 2) Hey! Take your meds with a full glass of water, please. Do it for Pippin, or Space Mom, or better yet, do it for yourself. 3) Ĝefeloað wē. We will carry on. 4) all funds from the sales of items at these two links will be sent to support charities aiding to fight for Trans rights in the US (not just T-shirts!) https://www.teepublic.com/t-shirt/74812801-all-conures-are-anarchists https://www.teepublic.com/t-shirt/74811778-whiptail-pride 5) Since multiple people have requested this over the last two weeks or so, my ko-fi is: https://ko-fi.com/codyandpippin

item.title: Good News-letter #10, October Edition!
item.description:
Happy post-Halloween to you guys, gals, and non-binary pals! I hope you’re doing well. Here’s a treat bucket full of good news for you!
Judge agrees that authors and other creatives can sue OpenAi for copyright infringement - https://screenrant.com/george-rr-martin-game-of-thrones-book-copyright-infrightment-lawsuit-update/
Governor Whitmer allocates funds for needy families, school lunches - https://www.wilx.com/2025/10/30/state-provide-45-million-feed-michiganders-amid-snap-benefits-pause/?outputType=amp
MIT refuses to take propaganda money - https://www.nbcnews.com/news/education/mit-rejects-trump-agenda-funding-benefits-rcna236894
Democrat wins position in Alaska Republicans controlled for a decade - https://www.newsweek.com/alaska-fairbanks-mayor-election-democrat-republican-10844700
Woman thriving post-divorce continues to give Bozo’s money to great causes - https://fortune.com/2025/10/10/billionaire-mackenzie-scott-doubles-down-on-dei-with-42-million-donation/
Until next time my friends! I love you and there’s nothing you can do about it! Have a good story needs sharing? Message me! Wanna get notified on the next one? Comment “count me in” below!
